<br>
Note when considering all strategies you must consider the fact that you can only play so many songs(duh)<br>
<br>
Strategies...<br>
<br>
Run around and never come into melee range and try to kill the rogue with just songs.  Well songs don't do very good dmg vs high resists.  While this is quite doable the rogue can just leave unless you think your going to play selos, amplification resist lowering songs (at least 2) snare + dd + dots or 9 songs.<br>
<br>
Go toe to toe and expect ds + songs to do him in. Several notes...<br>
<br>
Including other classes ds in this is just wrong its no more a good way to analyze bards in pvp than it would be to analyze rogues who have enc + cleric buffs.<br>
<br>
If your working in occasional selos and amplification + both dmg shields I wouldn't expect you to be able to play much more than that.<br>
<br>
If you try to go for just instruments in this case expect to die or more likely go into kite mode forcing the rogue to zone in disgust when the rogue jousts you with backstabs taking almost no ds dmg or with chaotic stabs for 120.  Btw don't tell me you can't be bsed there is no such thing as a player who can't be bsed.<br>
<br>
If you go for weapons instead of instruments the above still aplies except you will be able to do some dmg to the rogue as well.  Still I don't see you comming out ahead if the rogue is smart.<br>
<br>
The only way that I could see that a bard would be fearsome in pvp at high lvls is with a partner.  Huge lowering of mr + snare from the bard or partner = dead people.<br>
<br>
Also a few things to consider from the rogues perspective...<br>
<br>
Chaotic stab as listed above<br>
<br>
Jousting with backstabs as above<br>
<br>
Poisons, you can resist them with songs but this is yet another song to be played although I guess you can drop it after the initial combat round unless the rogue is joisting with bs and waiting.  Btw as far as I know (and I checked the spdat) there is no song that both adds a ds and pr.  Have to use a seperate song or gear.<br>
<br>
Disciplines.  The primary concern being duelist.  I know you can either run around, DA at 60, or use parry disc but this should be activated along with backstab and although those strategies will minimize the dmg it does you could easily be looking at from 550 up to a TON of dmg just from that initial round of combat with duelist.<br>
<br>
Indoors.  I'm sure you would never duel a rogue indoors just like i would never duel a bard outdoors (hey solution don't duel bards heh) but in pvp this can come up.  Any non selos zone leaves you in a VERY weak position.<br>
<br>
First off how many songs can a bard be expected to twist at once while still maintaining amplification and selos chorus and moving around to fight?<br>
<br>
Next without outside help OR buffs and while limited to the number of songs provided for the above question can you provide the ideal strategy for fighting a decently equiped lvl 60 rogue for...<br>
<br>
A) Pking a rogue even if he doesn't want to stick around.  BTW no rogue will want to stay and play when you try to kite with songs.<br>
<br>
B) Killing a rogue in a situation where he will stick around.  Not including kiting as the only method of dmg because this will lead to the rogue zoning.<br>
<br>
C) Trying to fight a rogue indoors.  IMO you will die pitifully regardless of what you do.<br>
<br>
A few nagging bugs with bards...<br>
<br>
Charm poofing pets<br>
<br>
Uninteruptable gate with a thurg gate potion. Solution make bs work like warrior kick )). <br>
